Its alot of fun. The graphics are great and the game runs smooth for me. You can change the sensitivity and button size from the option menu at the main menu. When you see the 3 save slots look under them and you'll see the 'option' button. You will see 'UI size' you can make the buttons bigger and you will see 'input' below that and thats how you can change the sensitivity. People were saying the buttons were to small and the sensitivity was to high and there isnt no way to change it.

The game runs very smoothly and gameplay is looking good, but there are several aspects that could enhance the game. 1) Lighting sucks: enemies only need to move back a few squares and they're out of sight. Everything dark; massive struggle. 2) Look/Turn control conflicts with Action UI Buttons. Several instances where my view tweaks out because I touched between the two action buttons and the game registers it as "look over there!" 3) Item distance vs. what I can interact with. While gameplay is fine, I found myself on several occasions trying to pick up an item barely out of my reach. With this, I thought it'd be a fine addition to still be able to hover over items, but to have the text read "Item out of reach" or something instead of looking around everywhere. 4) More turn and look bogus. While dragging from the right side of the screen makes a fine look around (going left), turning right is just a silly struggle. Perhaps make a fixed drag distance to register turning (so it's balanced) and maybe a "joystick" UI. The game is great on PC, but I really want to see it nailed down on the phone. :)

For those who don't know about this game, put into this perspective:Its like Minecraft when your delving into dungeons without any torches and barely any health at the start or Equipment.And yes,it has the awesomeness of minecraft because of randomely generated dungeons everytime,with surprises at every turn and difficulty increasing every floor you go down.This game also gets major points for looking and sounding like an old PC FPS dungeon crawler with no expert graphics,but instead coupled with good old school style primitive 3D blocks and sprites a'la DooM,where enemies are made of just few frame sprites and areas made out of simple 3D polygons.It looks real great,and is like Minecraft a parody of old style graphics you saw in Wolfenstein 3D and DooM/anything that uses said game engine. Like Minecraft also, the game is apparently moddable with custom texture packs for changing the look and adding custom maps, which can be made extremely simple. Plus everything this game packs, it can last a long time with new things all the time. Just needs PLAY optimization!
